race.comment: PAW PASCAL (7) is a talented type and proved too classy last time to win by a neck at Warragul in a handy 23.23 beating Just Angelic. Has performed well from this box with a win and five minor placings to his name from eight starts. Sure to prove hard to beat. NOLAN BALE (1) has been settling off the speed lately, finishing fourth (23.54) last time in a Grade 5 at Warragul. Form here sound including three wins. Likely to be about the money. SHEILA'S WAIT (5) showed good speed off a low draw but weakened and run over late when 5th over 390m at this track in Grade 5 company. Has a strong record out of this box with two wins and a minor placing from four starts. Must be included in calculations. FRANCESCA ROSE (2) looks an each-way chance.
